Not really a long doc...:-)

Not really a short one either...:-(

** Please read disclaimer at bottom of document. :-)

If you have only a 1MB amiga, you'll probably have to quit DuneII to run this
program.  It IS only programmed in blitz and seems to insist on being at least
50 kb long; how much of that actually resides IN memory when run, I don't know.

To use:

1)  Load DuneII, play it.
2)  When you run out of money, save the game. Remember what you call it.
3)  Goto the mentat screen and select something...doesn't matter what.
4)  Press <L-Amiga>-<N> to bring workbench to the front.
5)  Run DuneEd.
6)  When asked, find the directory you run DuneII from (or a save disk),
    using the (sad) file requester.  Ignore the CD button.
7)  You will then be asked for the name of the saved game. Enter it.
8)  Read the message.
9)  DuneEd will now quit.
10) If you are short on memory, close all the windows before 11)
11) Press <L-Amiga>-<M> until the mentat screen comes up.
12) Return to the game and reload the save game.
14) (I'm superstitious) Look at all the money!!!

Note: I can't be bothered to search for the maximum value of spice a silo can
      hold, so if you only have 3 silos, DuneEd will fill them up and the rest
      of the spice will be lost.

With this wonderful program you can now easily win DuneII using all three
of the great houses.

I doubt this program will ever be that popular but if I get anymore than
say...15 responses I might hack around a bit more, increase tank armour,
weapon power, etc..  Don't expect anything though, I won't.

If you really like this program, i.e. it has saved you from committing
suicide, etc. please feel free to send me money, computers (NOT P.C.s!!!!),
